      • isHit

        public boolean isHit()
        Description copied from interface: GetResult
        Decides if this get result represents a "hit", i.e. the search ended up in a concrete entry.

        This method returns false in case that no entry matched the query. It returns true if an entry matched the query, even if that entry represents a deletion.

        If this method returns true, then GetResult.getValue() will always return null (no match found). Otherwise, GetResult.getValue() may return null to indicate an explicit deletion, or a non- null value to indicate an insert/update.

        Specified by:
        isHit in interface GetResult<T>
        Returns:
        true if the search produced a concrete result, or false if no key matched the query.
